ratings.comment: As a 1-credit course, it expects way too much for what the class is about. Courses like this should be taught by someone who cares about career readiness and wants the best for students.

This was one of the most unexpectedly difficult classes I've taken, especially considering it's only one credit. The professor is an extremely tough grader no flexibility, and they do not make exceptions under any circumstances. Instructions were unclear and she was little to no help at all and didn't budge. I wouldn't recommend this class at all.
Runs her class like the navy
